{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BMdsXGwp2tL88vN9stt8Wj","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now let me create a comprehensive summary report of my findings.\n\n## Summary Report: Source Code Changes & Documentation Analysis\n\nBased on my thorough review of the modified/new source files and documentation, here are the key findings:\n\n### Source Code Changes\n\n#### 1. **Version Update**\n- **File:** `/workspace/internal/version/VERSION`\n- **Change:** Version bumped to `1.15.0` (previously 1.14.1)\n\n#### 2. **Configuration Additions** \n- **File:** `/workspace/internal/config/config.go`\n- **New Config Types:**\n  - `PopulationConfig` struct (lines 20-24):\n    - `Enabled bool` — master switch for population feature\n    - `Size int` — number of candidates to maintain (default 5)\n    - `PromotionThreshold float64` — fitness score to promote (0.0-1.0, default 0.8)\n  - `EvolutionConfig` extended with nested `Population PopulationConfig` field (line 31)\n\n#### 3. **Daemon Main** \n- **File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go`\n- **New Functions:**\n  - `initPopulation(globalCfg *config.Config) *evolution.Population` (lines 205-221)\n    - Loads population config from project directory\n    - Returns nil if not enabled\n  - **Initialization:** Lines 84-88 set up population and attach to gRPC server via `srv.SetPopulation(pop)`\n\n#### 4. **New Evolution Package: Population-Based Prompt Evolution**\n- **File:** `/workspace/internal/evolution/population.go` (new)\n- **Core Types:**\n  - `PopulationConfig` — configuration struct\n  - `Candidate` struct with fields:\n    - `ID string` — unique identifier\n    - `Content string` — prompt variant content\n    - `Fitness float64` — performance score (0.0-1.0)\n    - `Runs int` — number of times tested\n    - `Generation int` — which generation this variant is from\n    - `Promoted bool` — whether this candidate was promoted to base prompt\n    - `CreatedAt string` — timestamp\n  - `Assignment` struct — records which candidate was used for a run:\n    - `RunID string`\n    - `CandidateID string`\n    - `PromptPath string` — which prompt file this applies to\n    - `Snapshot string` — name of pre-candidate snapshot\n  - `Population` struct — manager for the population\n    - Maintains `assignments map[string]*Assignment` (run_id → assignment)\n    - Scoped by ProjectDir + WorkflowName\n\n- **Key Methods:**\n  - `LoadCandidates() []Candidate` — reads JSONL candidates file from `.cloche/evolution/population/{workflow}/candidates.jsonl`\n  - `SaveCandidates(candidates []Candidate)` — writes JSONL format\n  - `SelectCandidate() *Candidate` — fitness-proportionate selection with exploration bonus:\n    - Candidates with fewer runs get exploration boost (0.2 × (3 - runs) bonus)\n    - Selects from top-3 candidates with randomness\n  - `ApplyCandidate(candidate, promptPath, runID) *Assignment` — pre-run:\n    - Creates snapshot of original prompt\n    - Overwrites prompt file with candidate content\n    - Records assignment\n  - `ScoreAndPromote(runID, succeeded) (*Candidate, bool, error)` — post-run:\n    - Updates candidate's `Runs` count\n    - Updates `Fitness` using running average: `(oldFitness × (runs-1) + reward) / runs`\n    - Promotes if fitness >= threshold AND runs >= 2 AND not already promoted\n    - Promotion writes candidate content back to base prompt path\n  - `RestoreSnapshot(assignment)` — restores original prompt from snapshot after run\n  - `RecordAssignment(runID, assignment)`\n  - `GetAssignment(runID)`\n\n- **Storage Layout:**\n  - Population data: `.cloche/evolution/population/{workflow}/candidates.jsonl`\n  - Snapshots: `.cloche/evolution/snapshots/{timestamp}-pop-{filename}`\n\n#### 5. **Tests**\n- **File:** `/workspace/internal/evolution/population_test.go` (new)\n- **Test Coverage:**\n  - `TestPopulationSelectCandidate` — selection with/without candidates\n  - `TestPopulationLoadSaveCandidates` — JSONL persistence\n  - `TestPopulationApplyCandidate` — pre-run application and snapshots\n  - `TestPopulationRestoreSnapshot` — post-run restoration\n  - `TestPopulationScoreAndPromote` — fitness update and promotion logic\n  - `TestPopulationScoreNoPromotion` — below-threshold fitness\n  - `TestPopulationScoreNoAssignment` — graceful no-op\n  - `TestFirstPromptPath` — workflow parsing to find first prompt\n  - `TestPopulationEndToEnd` — full 4-run cycle with multiple candidates\n\n#### 6. **gRPC Server Integration**\n- **File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`\n- **Changes:**\n  - Field added: `population *evolution.Population` (line 42)\n  - Method: `SetPopulation(pop *evolution.Population)` (lines 81-83)\n  - **Pre-run hook** (lines 342-356):\n    - If population enabled and candidate available, select and apply\n    - Logs candidate application\n  - **Post-run hook** (lines 575-590):\n    - Calls `ScoreAndPromote` with run success status\n    - Logs fitness and promotion status\n    - Restores snapshot if not promoted\n\n### Documentation Status\n\n**Population/Candidate Feature:**\n- **Status:** COMPLETELY UNDOCUMENTED in docs/\n- No mentions in any `.md` files\n- Not referenced in system design, workflows, evolution design, or config design docs\n- Feature is fully implemented in code but not documented for users\n\n**Evolution Feature (Overall):**\n- **Design Doc:** `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md`\n  - Covers orchestration, reflection, prompt curation, script generation, DSL mutation\n  - No mention of population-based prompt evolution\n  - Focuses on post-run analysis and automatic workflow improvement\n- **Implementation Plan:** `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-implementation.md`\n  - Task-based implementation guide\n  - Does not mention population feature\n\n**Workflow DSL Docs:** `/workspace/docs/workflows.md`\n- No population-related syntax or configuration examples\n\n**Configuration Docs:** `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-config-toml-design.md`\n- Shows default `[evolution]` section with `debounce_seconds`, `min_confidence`, `max_prompt_bullets`\n- No `[evolution.population]` section shown\n- Defaults do not include population config keys\n\n### Key Technical Insights\n\n**Population Algorithm:**\n1. **Selection:** Fitness-proportionate with exploration bonus for under-tested candidates (Runs < 3 get 0.2 per untested run bonus)\n2. **Scoring:** Running average fitness: `fitness(n+1) = (fitness(n) × n + reward) / (n+1)` where reward = 1.0 if succeeded, 0.0 if failed\n3. **Promotion Criteria:** Fitness ≥ threshold (0.8 default) AND runs ≥ 2 AND not already promoted\n4. **Snapshot Mechanism:** Original prompt backed up before applying candidate; restored if not promoted\n\n**Integration Points:**\n- Pre-run: Select candidate, apply to prompt file (via `SelectCandidate` + `ApplyCandidate`)\n- Post-run: Score and check promotion, restore if needed (via `ScoreAndPromote` + `RestoreSnapshot`)\n- All operations scoped per project/workflow via `ProjectDir` + `WorkflowName`\n\n**Configuration Keys (New):**\n```toml\n[evolution.population]\nenabled = bool                     # default: off (must be explicitly enabled)\nsize = int                         # default: 5\npromotion_threshold = float64      # default: 0.8\n```\n\n### What's Missing from Documentation\n\n1. **Population feature overview** — what it does, how it works, when to use it\n2. **Configuration guide** — how to enable and tune population settings\n3. **Workflow integration** — how population selection affects prompt handling\n4. **Examples** — sample `config.toml` with population section\n5. **Use cases** — when prompt evolution via population is preferred over post-run analysis\n6. **Interaction with Evolution** — how population-based and post-run evolution work together (if at all)\n\nThis population feature appears to be a **genetic algorithm-style prompt optimization** system that runs in parallel with (or independent of) the post-run evolution analysis system."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a915d990c0ac0eb10 (use SendMessage with to: 'a915d990c0ac0eb10' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 52499\ntool_uses: 19\nduration_ms: 50197</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bde08716-55af-46e3-8699-03ed6e35c1ab","uuid":"ca0d0c8b-1634-4b30-aeab-2fc4be70368a","timestamp":"2026-03-17T14:16:48.753Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the current source code changes and existing documentation. Please:\n\n1. Read these modified/new files:\n   - cmd/cloched/main.go\n   - internal/adapters/grpc/server.go\n   - internal/config/config.go\n   - internal/version/VERSION\n   - internal/evolution/population.go\n   - internal/evolution/population_test.go\n\n2. Find and read documentation files:\n   - docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md\n   - docs/workflows.md\n   - Any other docs in docs/ directory\n\n3. Check for any references to \"evolution\", \"population\", \"fitness\", \"candidate\", \"selector\" in documentation files.\n\nReport back the key details from source changes (new types, functions, config keys, CLI flags) and what the docs currently say about evolution/population features.","agentId":"a915d990c0ac0eb10","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now let me create a comprehensive summary report of my findings.\n\n## Summary Report: Source Code Changes & Documentation Analysis\n\nBased on my thorough review of the modified/new source files and documentation, here are the key findings:\n\n### Source Code Changes\n\n#### 1. **Version Update**\n- **File:** `/workspace/internal/version/VERSION`\n- **Change:** Version bumped to `1.15.0` (previously 1.14.1)\n\n#### 2. **Configuration Additions** \n- **File:** `/workspace/internal/config/config.go`\n- **New Config Types:**\n  - `PopulationConfig` struct (lines 20-24):\n    - `Enabled bool` — master switch for population feature\n    - `Size int` — number of candidates to maintain (default 5)\n    - `PromotionThreshold float64` — fitness score to promote (0.0-1.0, default 0.8)\n  - `EvolutionConfig` extended with nested `Population PopulationConfig` field (line 31)\n\n#### 3. **Daemon Main** \n- **File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go`\n- **New Functions:**\n  - `initPopulation(globalCfg *config.Config) *evolution.Population` (lines 205-221)\n    - Loads population config from project directory\n    - Returns nil if not enabled\n  - **Initialization:** Lines 84-88 set up population and attach to gRPC server via `srv.SetPopulation(pop)`\n\n#### 4. **New Evolution Package: Population-Based Prompt Evolution**\n- **File:** `/workspace/internal/evolution/population.go` (new)\n- **Core Types:**\n  - `PopulationConfig` — configuration struct\n  - `Candidate` struct with fields:\n    - `ID string` — unique identifier\n    - `Content string` — prompt variant content\n    - `Fitness float64` — performance score (0.0-1.0)\n    - `Runs int` — number of times tested\n    - `Generation int` — which generation this variant is from\n    - `Promoted bool` — whether this candidate was promoted to base prompt\n    - `CreatedAt string` — timestamp\n  - `Assignment` struct — records which candidate was used for a run:\n    - `RunID string`\n    - `CandidateID string`\n    - `PromptPath string` — which prompt file this applies to\n    - `Snapshot string` — name of pre-candidate snapshot\n  - `Population` struct — manager for the population\n    - Maintains `assignments map[string]*Assignment` (run_id → assignment)\n    - Scoped by ProjectDir + WorkflowName\n\n- **Key Methods:**\n  - `LoadCandidates() []Candidate` — reads JSONL candidates file from `.cloche/evolution/population/{workflow}/candidates.jsonl`\n  - `SaveCandidates(candidates []Candidate)` — writes JSONL format\n  - `SelectCandidate() *Candidate` — fitness-proportionate selection with exploration bonus:\n    - Candidates with fewer runs get exploration boost