andidate available, select and apply\n    - Logs candidate application\n  - **Post-run hook** (lines 575-590):\n    - Calls `ScoreAndPromote` with run success status\n    - Logs fitness and promotion status\n    - Restores snapshot if not promoted\n\n### Documentation Status\n\n**Population/Candidate Feature:**\n- **Status:** COMPLETELY UNDOCUMENTED in docs/\n- No mentions in any `.md` files\n- Not referenced in system design, workflows, evolution design, or config design docs\n- Feature is fully implemented in code but not documented for users\n\n**Evolution Feature (Overall):**\n- **Design Doc:** `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md`\n  - Covers orchestration, reflection, prompt curation, script generation, DSL mutation\n  - No mention of population-based prompt evolution\n  - Focuses on post-run analysis and automatic workflow improvement\n- **Implementation Plan:** `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-implementation.md`\n  - Task-based implementation guide\n  - Does not mention population feature\n\n**Workflow DSL Docs:** `/workspace/docs/workflows.md`\n- No population-related syntax or configuration examples\n\n**Configuration Docs:** `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-config-toml-design.md`\n- Shows default `[evolution]` section with `debounce_seconds`, `min_confidence`, `max_prompt_bullets`\n- No `[evolution.population]` section shown\n- Defaults do not include population config keys\n\n### Key Technical Insights\n\n**Population Algorithm:**\n1. **Selection:** Fitness-proportionate with exploration bonus for under-tested candidates (Runs < 3 get 0.2 per untested run bonus)\n2. **Scoring:** Running average fitness: `fitness(n+1) = (fitness(n) × n + reward) / (n+1)` where reward = 1.0 if succeeded, 0.0 if failed\n3. **Promotion Criteria:** Fitness ≥ threshold (0.8 default) AND runs ≥ 2 AND not already promoted\n4. **Snapshot Mechanism:** Original prompt backed up before applying candidate; restored if not promoted\n\n**Integration Points:**\n- Pre-run: Select candidate, apply to prompt file (via `SelectCandidate` + `ApplyCandidate`)\n- Post-run: Score and check promotion, restore if needed (via `ScoreAndPromote` + `RestoreSnapshot`)\n- All operations scoped per project/workflow via `ProjectDir` + `WorkflowName`\n\n**Configuration Keys (New):**\n```toml\n[evolution.population]\nenabled = bool                     # default: off (must be explicitly enabled)\nsize = int                         # default: 5\npromotion_threshold = float64      # default: 0.8\n```\n\n### What's Missing from Documentation\n\n1. **Population feature overview** — what it does, how it works, when to use it\n2. **Configuration guide** — how to enable and tune population settings\n3. **Workflow integration** — how population selection affects prompt handling\n4. **Examples** — sample `config.toml` with population section\n5. **Use cases** — when prompt evolution via population is preferred over post-run analysis\n6. **Interaction with Evolution** — how population-based and post-run evolution work together (if at all)\n\nThis population feature appears to be a **genetic algorithm-style prompt optimization** system that runs in parallel with (or independent of) the post-run evolution analysis system."}],"totalDurationMs":50197,"totalTokens":52499,"totalToolUseCount":19,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":181,"cache_read_input_tokens":50159,"output_tokens":2156,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":181},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
