{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01M2mdvpoRArkgmm92JHo4t1","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Project Settings File: config.toml\n     2→\n     3→**Date:** 2026-03-06\n     4→**Status:** Design\n     5→\n     6→## Problem\n     7→\n     8→The per-project settings file is `.cloche/config` with no extension, making it\n     9→ambiguous and inconsistent with the TOML library in use.\n    10→\n    11→## Change\n    12→\n    13→Rename to `.cloche/config.toml`. No backwards compatibility with the old filename.\n    14→\n    15→## Default file (created by `cloche init`)\n    16→\n    17→```toml\n    18→# Cloche project configuration\n    19→\n    20→[orchestration]\n    21→concurrency        = 1\n    22→stagger_seconds    = 1.0\n    23→# list_tasks_command = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh\"\n    24→# dedup_seconds    = 300\n    25→# max_consecutive_failures = 3\n    26→\n    27→[evolution]\n    28→enabled           = true\n    29→debounce_seconds  = 30\n    30→min_confidence    = \"medium\"\n    31→max_prompt_bullets = 50\n    32→\n    33→[evolution.population]\n    34→# enabled            = false\n    35→# size               = 5\n    36→# promotion_threshold = 0.8\n    37→```\n    38→\n    39→Notes:\n    40→- `orchestration.concurrency` defaults to `1` (single run at a time).\n    41→- `orchestration.stagger_seconds` adds delay between consecutive launches (default `1.0`).\n    42→- `orchestration.list_tasks_command` (optional) is a shell command that outputs a JSON array of\n    43→  task objects (`[{\"id\":\"...\",\"title\":\"...\",\"description\":\"...\"}]`). When set, the daemon\n    44→  picks tasks and passes the ID via `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var.\n    45→- `orchestration.dedup_seconds` (default `300`) prevents reassignment of the same task ID\n    46→  within the timeout window.\n    47→- `orchestration.max_consecutive_failures` (default `3`, must be > 0) halts the\n    48→  orchestration loop after N consecutive failed runs (e.g. auth failures). Cleared on\n    49→  any successful run or via `cloche loop resume`.\n    50→- Commented-out keys show optional overrides that rarely need changing.\n    51→\n    52→## Code changes\n    53→\n    54→| File | Change |\n    55→|------|--------|\n    56→| `internal/config/config.go` | `Load()`: change path from `\"config\"` to `\"config.toml\"` |\n    57→| `cmd/cloche/init.go` | Add `config.toml` to the files created by init |\n    58→| `.cloche/config` (existing file in this repo) | Rename to `.cloche/config.toml` |\n    59→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bde08716-55af-46e3-8699-03ed6e35c1ab","uuid":"ffe78fee-a359-47cc-aaa8-5c3d5d0a396a","timestamp":"2026-03-17T14:17:37.187Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-config-toml-design.md","content":"# Project Settings File: config.toml\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-06\n**Status:** Design\n\n## Problem\n\nThe per-project settings file is `.cloche/config` with no extension, making it\nambiguous and inconsistent with the TOML library in use.\n\n## Change\n\nRename to `.cloche/config.toml`. No backwards compatibility with the old filename.\n\n## Default file (created by `cloche init`)\n\n```toml\n# Cloche project configuration\n\n[orchestration]\nconcurrency        = 1\nstagger_seconds    = 1.0\n# list_tasks_command = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh\"\n# dedup_seconds    = 300\n# max_consecutive_failures = 3\n\n[evolution]\nenabled           = true\ndebounce_seconds  = 30\nmin_confidence    = \"medium\"\nmax_prompt_bullets = 50\n\n[evolution.population]\n# enabled            = false\n# size               = 5\n# promotion_threshold = 0.8\n```\n\nNotes:\n- `orchestration.concurrency` defaults to `1` (single run at a time).\n- `orchestration.stagger_seconds` adds delay between consecutive launches (default `1.0`).\n- `orchestration.list_tasks_command` (optional) is a shell command that outputs a JSON array of\n  task objects (`[{\"id\":\"...\",\"title\":\"...\",\"description\":\"...\"}]`). When set, the daemon\n  picks tasks and passes the ID via `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var.\n- `orchestration.dedup_seconds` (default `300`) prevents reassignment of the same task ID\n  within the timeout window.\n- `orchestration.max_consecutive_failures` (default `3`, must be > 0) halts the\n  orchestration loop after N consecutive failed runs (e.g. auth failures). Cleared on\n  any successful run or via `cloche loop resume`.\n- Commented-out keys show optional overrides that rarely need changing.\n\n## Code changes\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `internal/config/config.go` | `Load()`: change path from `\"config\"` to `\"config.toml\"` |\n| `cmd/cloche/init.go` | Add `config.toml` to the files created by init |\n| `.cloche/config` (existing file in this repo) | Rename to `.cloche/config.toml` |\n","numLines":59,"startLine":1,"totalLines":59}}}
