{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012HdBKR5FULTbjZUWMBH6N7","type":"tool_result","content":"   440→```toml\n   441→[evolution]\n   442→enabled = true                # master switch\n   443→debounce_seconds = 30         # wait after last run before analyzing\n   444→min_confidence = \"medium\"     # minimum lesson confidence to act on\n   445→max_prompt_bullets = 50       # cap on knowledge bullets per prompt\n   446→```\n   447→\n   448→Evolution is enabled by default. Users can disable it per-project for static\n   449→workflows.\n   450→\n   451→## Population-Based Prompt Evolution\n   452→\n   453→In addition to the post-run reflective pipeline above, Cloche supports\n   454→**population-based prompt evolution** — a genetic-algorithm-style system that\n   455→maintains a pool of prompt variant candidates and selects among them for each\n   456→run.\n   457→\n   458→### How It Works\n   459→\n   460→1. **Pre-run selection:** Before a container starts, the daemon calls\n   461→   `SelectCandidate()` which uses fitness-proportionate selection with an\n   462→   exploration bonus for under-tested candidates (runs < 3 get a 0.2-per-missing-run\n   463→   bonus). The selected candidate's content replaces the base prompt file, and a\n   464→   snapshot of the original is saved.\n   465→2. **Post-run scoring:** After the run completes, `ScoreAndPromote()` updates\n   466→   the candidate's fitness using a running average:\n   467→   `fitness(n) = (fitness(n-1) × (n-1) + reward) / n` where reward is 1.0 on\n   468→   success and 0.0 on failure.\n   469→3. **Promotion:** If a candidate's fitness meets the promotion threshold\n   470→   (default 0.8) and it has been tested at least twice, its content is written\n   471→   back to the base prompt path permanently. Otherwise the original prompt is\n   472→   restored from the snapshot.\n   473→\n   474→### On-Disk State\n   475→\n   476→Population data is scoped by project and workflow:\n   477→\n   478→```\n   479→.cloche/\n   480→  evolution/\n   481→    population/\n   482→      <workflow>/\n   483→        candidates.jsonl       # one JSON object per candidate\n   484→    snapshots/\n   485→      <timestamp>-pop-<file>   # pre-candidate prompt backups\n   486→```\n   487→\n   488→Each candidate record contains: `ID`, `Content`, `Fitness`, `Runs`,\n   489→`Generation`, `Promoted`, `CreatedAt`.\n   490→\n   491→### Configuration\n   492→\n   493→```toml\n   494→[evolution.population]\n   495→enabled              = false   # opt-in (disabled by default)\n   496→size                 = 5       # number of candidates to maintain\n   497→promotion_threshold  = 0.8     # fitness score required for promotion (0.0–1.0)\n   498→```\n   499→\n   500→### Interaction with Post-Run Evolution\n   501→\n   502→Population selection and the reflective pipeline (Collector → Classifier →\n   503→Reflector → Curator/Script/DSL) operate independently. Population modifies the\n   504→prompt file *before* the run; the reflective pipeline modifies prompt files\n   505→*after* the run based on accumulated lessons. Both use the snapshot mechanism\n   506→for safe rollback.\n   507→\n   508→## Future Work (Out of Scope)\n   509→\n   510→- **Step removal/mutation** — modifying or removing existing step definitions\n   511→  (higher risk, needs careful design around backwards compatibility)\n   512→- **`cloche evolve --revert <evo-id>`** — automated revert from snapshots\n   513→- **Helpfulness tracking** — automatically detecting whether applied lessons\n   514→  actually reduced failure rates, and pruning unhelpful ones\n   515→- **Cross-project learning** — sharing knowledge base insights across projects\n   516→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bde08716-55af-46e3-8699-03ed6e35c1ab","uuid":"c0248790-ece8-4c01-b93c-d462d5e28066","timestamp":"2026-03-17T14:17:37.636Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md","content":"```toml\n[evolution]\nenabled = true                # master switch\ndebounce_seconds = 30         # wait after last run before analyzing\nmin_confidence = \"medium\"     # minimum lesson confidence to act on\nmax_prompt_bullets = 50       # cap on knowledge bullets per prompt\n```\n\nEvolution is enabled by default. Users can disable it per-project for static\nworkflows.\n\n## Population-Based Prompt Evolution\n\nIn addition to the post-run reflective pipeline above, Cloche supports\n**population-based prompt evolution** — a genetic-algorithm-style system that\nmaintains a pool of prompt variant candidates and selects among them for each\nrun.\n\n### How It Works\n\n1. **Pre-run selection:** Before a container starts, the daemon calls\n   `SelectCandidate()` which uses fitness-proportionate selection with an\n   exploration bonus for under-tested candidates (runs < 3 get a 0.2-per-missing-run\n   bonus). The selected candidate's content replaces the base prompt file, and a\n   snapshot of the original is saved.\n2. **Post-run scoring:** After the run completes, `ScoreAndPromote()` updates\n   the candidate's fitness using a running average:\n   `fitness(n) = (fitness(n-1) × (n-1) + reward) / n` where reward is 1.0 on\n   success and 0.0 on failure.\n3. **Promotion:** If a candidate's fitness meets the promotion threshold\n   (default 0.8) and it has been tested at least twice, its content is written\n   back to the base prompt path permanently. Otherwise the original prompt is\n   restored from the snapshot.\n\n### On-Disk State\n\nPopulation data is scoped by project and workflow:\n\n```\n.cloche/\n  evolution/\n    population/\n      <workflow>/\n        candidates.jsonl       # one JSON object per candidate\n    snapshots/\n      <timestamp>-pop-<file>   # pre-candidate prompt backups\n```\n\nEach candidate record contains: `ID`, `Content`, `Fitness`, `Runs`,\n`Generation`, `Promoted`, `CreatedAt`.\n\n### Configuration\n\n```toml\n[evolution.population]\nenabled              = false   # opt-in (disabled by default)\nsize                 = 5       # number of candidates to maintain\npromotion_threshold  = 0.8     # fitness score required for promotion (0.0–1.0)\n```\n\n### Interaction with Post-Run Evolution\n\nPopulation selection and the reflective pipeline (Collector → Classifier →\nReflector → Curator/Script/DSL) operate independently. Population modifies the\nprompt file *before* the run; the reflective pipeline modifies prompt files\n*after* the run based on accumulated lessons. Both use the snapshot mechanism\nfor safe rollback.\n\n## Future Work (Out of Scope)\n\n- **Step removal/mutation** — modifying or removing existing step definitions\n  (higher risk, needs careful design around backwards compatibility)\n- **`cloche evolve --revert <evo-id>`** — automated revert from snapshots\n- **Helpfulness tracking** — automatically detecting whether applied lessons\n  actually reduced failure rates, and pruning unhelpful ones\n- **Cross-project learning** — sharing knowledge base insights across projects\n","numLines":77,"startLine":440,"totalLines":516}}}
